# DATA

## BAM Files

The aligned sequencing reads (BAM) for both strains can be downloaded from Caenorhabditis elegans Natural Diversity Resource:

- N2.bam and N2.bam.bai: https://caendr.org/isotype/N2/
- ECA712.bam and ECA712.bam.bai: https://caendr.org/isotype/ECA712/

Place BAM files and their index files in: data/bam/

## Reference Genome and Annotation

Reference genome and annotation files are from Ensembl release 115. Download and place in data/reference/:

- dna.toplevel.fa → https://ftp.ensembl.org/pub/release-115/fasta/caenorhabditis_elegans/dna/
- genes.gtf → https://ftp.ensembl.org/pub/release-115/gtf/caenorhabditis_elegans/
- CDS.fa → https://ftp.ensembl.org/pub/release-115/fasta/caenorhabditis_elegans/cds/
- protein.fa → https://ftp.ensembl.org/pub/release-115/fasta/caenorhabditis_elegans/pep/

Place all reference files in: data/reference/

  
